You said: how to print subarrays of size kTo print all contiguous subarrays of a specific size k, you use a sliding window technique. Iterate through the array with a starting index from 0 up to n-k (where n is array length), and print the k consecutive elements from that start point.Python Implementationpythondef print_subarrays_of_size_k(arr, k):
    n = len(arr)
    if k > n or k <= 0:
        print("Invalid size")
        return

    # Loop from the beginning to n - k
    for i in range(n - k + 1):
        # Print the subarray of size k starting at index i
        subarray = arr[i : i + k]
        print(subarray)

# Example Usage
arr = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
k = 3
print_subarrays_of_size_k(arr, k)

